Subject: [RFC PATCH v1 0/4] arm64: dts: apple: add T6040 J614s support

This RFC collects the current minimal device-tree description for the
14-inch M4 Pro MacBook Pro (Mac16,8 / J614s).  It deliberately excludes the
experimental USB and ANS/storage nodes used by the local bring-up branch.

The base DT describes the measured 14-core topology (including the disabled
positional CPU slot), the generated PMGR power domains, and the MTP transport.
Separate variants enable the built-in keyboard/trackpad and the DebugUSB
DockChannel serial path.  The latter uses measured AIC input 816 and explicit
per-instance RX masks: BIT(1) for the UART and BIT(3) for MTP.

The series compiles all three DTBs.  CHECK_DTBS=y requires the existing
T6041 PMGR binding prerequisite.  Remaining RFC-level schema dependencies are
T6040 AIC and watchdog, T8140 ASC mailbox, and the not-yet-upstream
DockChannel/HID/serial bindings.  The DebugUSB variant is therefore last and
is not intended as a normal production board DT.

The T6040 description was also compared with yuka's current
feature/m4-m5-minimal-device-trees branch.  That branch covers J773s and a
different T6040 CPU layout; it does not contain the J614s board, PMGR corpus,
or measured DockChannel IRQ/mask data included here.

CJ Damsleth (4):
